Stage 0.Title: Analyze and Classify Elements
Stage 0.Objectives: Analyze input elements to identify, evaluate, and classify their defining attributes and relationships in preparation for output derivation.

Stage 1.Title: derive target output
Stage 1.Objectives: Derive target outputs by applying defined transformations, operations, or mappings under specified rules to the classified inputs.

Stage 2.Title: Compute Quantitative or Conditional Measure
Stage 2.Objectives: Compute necessary quantitative or conditional measures by applying defined transformations and criteria to the derived outputs or intermediate values.

Stage 3.Title: select elements by criteria conformity
Stage 3.Objectives: Evaluate and select the elements that meet or fail specified criteria, prioritizing those that best satisfy the conditions to finalize the result set.

Stage 1.Objectives: Identify and prioritize elements that meet multiple criteria, extract their key features, and apply transformations to produce variant configurations.
